</span><span class='line'>  <span class="nt">&lt;li&gt;&lt;a</span> <span class="na">href=</span><span class="s">&quot;/about&quot;</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>About<span class="nt">&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">&lt;/ul&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">&lt;p&gt;</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></p>

<h3>6. Converting Markdown to HTML and preview</h3>

<pre><code>$ rake generate  
$ rake preview  
</code></pre>

<p>Head to <code>http://localhost:4000</code> to preview site.</p>

<h3>7. Deploy on Heroku and view</h3>

<p>Create a git remote name &ldquo;<strong>heroku</strong>&rdquo; to point to you git respository on Heroku:
<code>
$ git config branch.master.remote heroku  
</code></p>

<p>Commit and deploy onto Heroku:
<code>
$ git add .
$ git commit -m "some update"
$ git push heroku master    
$ heroku open  
</code></p>

<p>If you need tips on setting up Heroku check out the guide <a href="http://somelink.com" title="Guide to setting up Heroku">here</a>.</p>

<p>Also you can find more details on setting up your own domain name <a href="http://somelink.com" title="Setting up your domain name">here</a>.</p>

